  "summary": "OpenAI provides Text‑to‑Speech capabilities through its API, allowing developers to convert text to natural‑sounding audio in real time or offline. The API exposes voices and audio formats suitable for web and mobile use and integrates with broader OpenAI platform features used alongside chat, vision, and tools. Documentation includes code samples for Node.js and Python, plus streaming examples that demonstrate low‑latency playback in browsers.\n\nCommon applications include voice features in chat apps, assistive reading, game dialogue prototyping, and narration for short clips. Developers control parameters such as voice selection and audio format, and can combine TTS with STT and conversation logic to build full duplex voice experiences. Pricing is usage‑based per generated audio. \n\nThe TTS API is best for teams that already use OpenAI’s platform and want a straightforward way to add voice output to apps without managing separate TTS vendors or infrastructure.",
